{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AJFXYsHHxHhTgwRwxmDxku","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# mongodb/password-rotation\n2\t# Rotate MongoDB user password and update the corresponding Secret\n3\t\n4\tparams:\n5\t  cluster_prefix:\n6\t    default: mongodb-replica\n7\t    description: StatefulSet name of the replica set members.\n8\t  replica_set_name:\n9\t    default: mongodb-replica\n10\t    description: MongoDB replica set _id used when initiating the set.\n11\t  admin_secret_name:\n12\t    default: admin-user-password\n13\t    description: Kubernetes Secret holding the admin user's password.\n14\t  app_secret_name:\n15\t    default: app-user-password\n16\t    description: Kubernetes Secret holding the app user's current password.\n17\t  app_next_secret_name:\n18\t    default: app-user-password-next\n19\t    description: Kubernetes Secret holding the app user's next password.\n20\t  reporting_secret_name:\n21\t    default: reporting-user-password\n22\t    description: Kubernetes Secret holding the reporting user's password.\n23\t  admin_username:\n24\t    default: admin-user\n25\t    description: Username of the MongoDB admin user.\n26\t  app_username:\n27\t    default: app-user\n28\t    description: Username of the application user being rotated.\n29\t  reporting_username:\n30\t    default: reporting-user\n31\t    description: Username of the reporting user.\n32\t  app_database:\n33\t    default: appdb\n34\t    description: Application database that must remain accessible.\n35\t  app_collection:\n36\t    default: testdata\n37\t    description: Application collection seeded with data.\n38\t\n39\tprompt: |\n40\t  A 3-member MongoDB replica set is running in the mongodb namespace.\n41\t  Authentication is enabled. Passwords are stored in these Secrets:\n42\t  - {{params.admin_secret_name}}\n43\t  - {{params.app_secret_name}}\n44\t  - {{params.app_next_secret_name}}\n45\t  - {{params.reporting_secret_name}}\n46\t\n47\t  Task:\n48\t  - Rotate {{params.app_username}} to the password in {{params.app_next_secret_name}}.\n49\t  - Update the {{params.app_secret_name}} Secret to match the new password.\n50\t  - Do not break {{params.reporting_username}} or admin access.\n51\t  - Data in {{params.app_database}}.{{params.app_collection}} must remain accessible.\n52\t\n53\t  Notes:\n54\t  - Do not use operators or CRDs.\n55\t\n56\tnamespace_contract:\n57\t  required_roles: []\n58\t\n59\tmetrics:\n60\t  - time_to_first_mutation\n61\t\n62\tpreconditionUnits:\n63\t  - name: mongo_env_ready\n64\t    on_probe_fail: skip\n65\t    probe:\n66\t      # AUTHORITATIVE skip-if-running probe (P32): succeed when the canonical\n67\t      # StatefulSet exists OR any pod is Running, so the destructive namespace\n68\t      # rebuild below is skipped on an inherited cluster even if its pods are\n69\t      # momentarily not Running (mid-restart from a prior stage) -- the\n70\t      # StatefulSet persists across that window. The bare `grep -c Running`\n71\t      # could miss such a cluster and clobber inherited state.\n72\t      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n mongodb get statefulset {{params.cluster_prefix}} >/dev/null 2>&1 || kubectl -n mongodb get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -q Running'\"\n73\t        timeout_sec: 10\n74\t    apply:\n75\t      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl delete namespace mongodb --ignore-not-found=true; kubectl wait --for=delete namespace/mongodb --timeout=120s || true'\"\n76\t        sleep: 2\n77\t      - command: \"kubectl create namespace mongodb\"\n78\t        sleep: 1\n79\t      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb apply -f cases/mongodb/password-rotation/resource/secrets.yaml\"\n80\t        sleep: 1\n81\t      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb apply -f cases/mongodb/password-rotation/resource/services.yaml\"\n82\t        sleep: 1\n83\t      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb apply -f cases/mongodb/password-rotation/resource/statefulset.yaml\"\n84\t        sleep: 5\n85\t      - command: |\n86\t          /bin/sh -c 'for i in $(seq 1 120); do ready=$(kubectl -n mongodb get sts {{params.cluster_prefix}} -o jsonpath='\\''{.status.readyReplicas}'\\'' 2>/dev/null); if [ \"${ready:-0}\" -ge 3 ]; then exit 0; fi; sleep 5; done; exit 1'\n87\t        sleep: 2\n88\t      # Pod-Ready != mongod accepting TCP (§1.10): ping-until-ok before rs.initiate.\n89\t      - command: |\n90\t          /bin/sh -c 'for i in $(seq 1 30); do kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet --eval '\\''db.runCommand({ping:1}).ok'\\'' 2>/dev/null | grep -q 1 && exit 0; sleep 3; done; exit 1'\n91\t        sleep: 2\n92\t      - command: |\n93\t          /bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet --eval '\\''rs.initiate({_id:\"{{params.replica_set_name}}\",members:[{_id:0,host:\"mongodb-replica-0.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017\"},{_id:1,host:\"mongodb-replica-1.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017\"},{_id:2,host:\"mongodb-replica-2.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017\"}]})'\\'''\n94\t        sleep: 5\n95\t      - command: |\n96\t          /bin/sh -c 'for i in $(seq 1 20); do kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet --eval '\\''db.hello().isWritablePrimary'\\'' | grep true && exit 0; sleep 3; done; exit 1'\n97\t        sleep: 2\n98\t      - command: |\n99\t          /bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet --eval '\\''db.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").createUser({user:\"{{params.admin_username}}\",pwd:\"admin123password\",roles:[{role:\"clusterAdmin\",db:\"admin\"},{role:\"userAdminAnyDatabase\",db:\"admin\"},{role:\"readWriteAnyDatabase\",db:\"admin\"}]})'\\'''\n100\t        sleep: 2\n101\t      - command: |\n102\t          /bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet \"mongodb://{{params.admin_username}}:admin123password@localhost:27017/admin\" --eval '\\''db.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").createUser({user:\"{{params.app_username}}\",p