{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01A2yzUpgnnqKZTUgKqorpZ9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the setup more clearly. In line 102:\n```\ndb.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").createUser({user:\"app-user\",pwd:\"appuser123password\",roles:[{role:\"readWrite\",db:\"appdb\"}]})\n```\n\nThis creates the user in the `admin` database. But the system.users query shows `db: 'appdb'` and `_id: 'appdb.app-user'`!\n\nWait, that's strange. Let me re-read. Actually the user is being created with `db.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").createUser(...)`. \n\nSo `getSiblingDB(\"admin\")` switches to the admin database context, but looking at the system.users output, the user document shows it's actually stored in the `appdb` database with the `_id` of `appdb.app-user`. That's confusing because the command explicitly switched to admin before creating the user.\n\nThe user has both `dbAdmin` and `readWrite` roles on `appdb`, though the test.yaml only specifies `readWrite` — the `dbAdmin` role must have been added in an earlier workflow stage. Since the user is in `appdb`, the authSource should be `appdb`, but I already tried that connection string and it failed. Let me reconsider what's happening here — the precondition logs show that `admin_user_fixture` passed (so the admin user was already working), and `mongo_seed_fixture` also seemed to pass initially but then apply ran anyway. Let me check what the `admin_user_fixture` verify step actually does. Since I've confirmed that the admin user with `admin123password` authenticates successfully, that fixture is working correctly. The issue is with the app-user — it exists in MongoDB under `appdb` with the right structure, but authentication fails even though the password should be `appuser123password` from the secrets. I'm wondering if the user was created with a different password in an earlier stage, or if there's a mismatch I'm missing. Let me trace back through the precondition log to see if there's an `app_user_fixture` that ran before this test.\n\nActually, wait — the app-user has both `dbAdmin` and `readWrite` roles on `appdb`, which suggests it might have been modified by a prior stage. If this workflow has multiple stages and we're currently on stage_10, a previous stage could have rotated the password. That would explain why `appuser123password` isn't working — it might not be the current live password anymore. I need to check the workflow state to see what happened in the earlier stages.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4088,"cache_read_input_tokens":48043,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4088},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"239b7986-c9dd-48f8-b32e-77b5badc92ba","uuid":"53d7d187-05f1-4098-9ad8-392d9d0994da","request_id":"req_011CcghtG7XsyfgyvScHpzXL"}
